P95.AI — Intelligent Lead Qualification & Outbound System
Product Documentation
________________________________________
1. Overview
P95.AI is an enterprise-grade outbound intelligence platform designed to streamline lead generation, qualification, scoring, and outreach automation.
The system transforms raw prospect data into high-quality, outreach-ready leads through a structured pipeline powered by configurable ICP logic, transparent scoring, and automated messaging workflows.
This platform is built for GTM teams that require:
•	Signal-driven targeting
•	Scalable outbound workflows
•	Transparent decision systems
•	Clean, actionable UI
________________________________________
2. Core System Workflow
The platform operates across a structured lifecycle:
1.	Lead Sourcing (200+ prospects)
2.	Data Enrichment
3.	ICP-Based Qualification
4.	Scoring & Grading
5.	Outreach Generation
6.	Engagement Tracking (Analytics)
Each stage is modular, configurable, and visible within the admin interface.
________________________________________


3. Platform Architecture

3.1 ICP Configuration Engine
Admins define Ideal Customer Profile using structured dropdown-based controls:
Inputs:
•	Industries (multi-select + priority)
•	Regions (multi-select + tiering)
•	Company Size
•	Revenue Range
•	Company Maturity
•	Engineering Team Size
Output:
Filtered qualification criteria used in scoring + pipeline filtering.
________________________________________
3.2 Lead Pipeline (4-Stage System)
Stage 1: Source Collection
•	Clay Tables
•	Apollo
Tracks source contribution.
________________________________________
Stage 2: Enrichment Layer
Adds:
•	Emails
•	Job Titles
•	Tech Stack Signals
•	Revenue Data
•	Hiring Signals
Displays enrichment coverage

Stage 3: Qualification Layer
Applies:
•	ICP filters
•	Signal detection
•	Score logic
Outputs:
•	Qualified Leads
•	Rejected Leads
•	Pending Leads
________________________________________
Stage 4: Outreach-Ready Leads
Segmented into:
•	Hot
•	Warm
•	Cold
________________________________________
3.3 Lead Scoring Engine
Admin-configurable scoring model.
Signal Categories:
•	Firmographic Fit
•	Technographic Signals
•	Hiring Velocity
•	Growth Indicators
•	Compliance Exposure
Example Score Breakdown:
•	Company Size Match: +15
•	ML Hiring: +18
•	Funding Event: +20
•	Industry Match: +22
•	Stack Fit: +10
Total Score: 85 (Hot Lead)
________________________________________
Score Thresholds:
•	Hot: 80–100
•	Warm: 50–79
•	Cold: 0–49
________________________________________
3.4 Criteria Qualification Engine
Allows filtering leads by specific signal combinations.
Example:
Funding + ML Hiring + Healthcare → returns high-intent leads.
Displays:
•	Lead Name
•	Criteria Matched
•	Score Contribution
•	Tier
________________________________________
3.5 Score Simulation Mode
Admins can simulate scoring changes without altering live data.
Example:
•	ML Hiring Weight: 18 → 25
Dashboard updates instantly for scenario analysis.
________________________________________





3.6 Outreach Automation System
Default Behavior:
•	Auto-generates cold email for qualified leads
•	Uses dynamic tokens:
o	{{company_name}}
o	{{hiring_signal}}
o	{{funding_event}}
o	{{tech_stack_signal}}

Editing Workflow:
•	Each email includes ✏ Edit icon
•	Opens inline modal editor
•	Editable fields:
o	Subject
o	Body
o	CTA
o	Tone
o	Length
________________________________________
Workflow:
Lead Qualified → Email Generated → Edit → Save → Send
________________________________________
3.7 A/B Testing Panel
Supports experimentation across top 20 leads.
Features:
•	Variant A vs Variant B
•	Edit / Duplicate / Rename
•	Predicted response insights
•	Hypothesis display
________________________________________

